Search for a newline character in a string:

Copy
let str = "Visit Demo2s.com.\nLearn JavaScript.";
let patt1 = /\n/;
let result = str.search(patt1);
console.log(result);
Output:


Description
The \n character can find a newline character.

\n returns the position where the newline character was found.

If no match is found, it returns -1.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
\n	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
new RegExp("\\n") or simply: /\n/
